# ── Credential stores and CLI keyrings ───────────────────────────────────────
# Machine-specific auth state created by CLI tools. These are runtime artifacts,
# not configuration — they must never roam via chezmoi or Syncthing.
# Pattern: if a CLI tool creates a directory or file in ~ to store auth tokens,
# it belongs here. Add entries as tools enter the stack, with the actual path
# the tool creates (verify with `ls ~/` after first auth).
#
# Current:
infisical-keyring                  # Infisical CLI fallback keyring (WSL/headless)
#
# Additional providers:
.config/op                       # 1Password CLI
.aws                             # AWS CLI credentials and config
.config/gcloud                   # Google Cloud SDK auth state
.azure                           # Azure CLI auth tokens
.config/github-copilot           # GitHub Copilot CLI
.kube/config                     # kubectl — contains cluster credentials

